  "id": "019d2dfe-9390-7b72-bc61-d37b8b5ea397",
  "content": "# Tiered Knowledge System — Complete Domain Map (Research Synthesis)\n\n## Domain 1: Memory Type Classification (DECIDED)\n5 types: Structural, Decisional, Episodic, Analytical, Procedural\nEach type has a distinct decay profile (alpha values for power-law decay).\n\n## Domain 2: Tier Lifecycle (DECIDED)\n4 tiers: Hot (HNSW indexed) → Warm (HNSW indexed, deprioritized) → Cold (not in HNSW, embedding preserved, reversible) → Forgotten (compacted into summary)\nCold is reversible — entries auto-promote on access.\n\n## Domain 3: Access Tracking\n- Two tiers of access: Tier 1 (returned to agent) and Tier 2 (candidate but filtered)\n- Entry-level fields: last_accessed, access_count, access_agents (u8), decay_score (f32)\n- In-memory DashMap buffer with periodic Redb flush (every 60s or 256 entries)\n- Agent breadth > raw count: 5 different agents accessing > 5 accesses by same agent\n- EMA-based decay scoring with configurable half-life\n\n## Domain 4: Decay Mathematics\n- Power-law R = (1+t)^(-alpha) preferred over exponential (fat tail preserves cold entries)\n- Alpha values: Structural=0, Procedural=0.10, Decisional=0.15, Analytical=0.30, Episodic=0.60\n- Composite score: recency + importance + access_frequency + graph_connectivity\n- Confidence modulates decay: effective_age = actual_age / confidence\n- Thresholds with hysteresis: Hot>=0.50, Warm>=0.25, Cold>=0.05, promotion gap=0.10\n\n## Domain 5: Forgetting Policies\n- 3-level config hierarchy: global → per-scope → per-memory-type\n- 4 policy types: age-based, inactivity-based, combined, budget-based (top-N)\n- Pinning mechanism: explicit pin + auto-protection rules (decisions, high-connectivity, chain heads)\n- Gradual transition via continuous strength scoring, not cliff drops\n- Safety: never compact chain HEADs, never compact entries younger than type's max_age\n\n## Domain 6: Compaction Strategy\n- Walk supersession chain, LLM-summarize preserving final state + key rationale\n- New summary entry with compacted_from metadata, new embedding\n- Originals archived (JSON preserved, embedding discarded)\n- Warning: Knowledge Objects paper documents 60% knowledge loss from cascading compaction — be conservative\n\n## Domain 7: HNSW Index Management\n- hnsw_rs has NO deletion support — current orphan+rebuild approach is correct\n- Blue-green rebuild: build new index in background, atomic swap under mutex\n- Cold entries: brute-force cosine scan (< 2ms for 3K entries at 768-dim)\n- Async promotion: return cold hit immediately, spawn background HNSW re-insertion\n- PostgresStore: partial HNSW indexes with WHERE clause (pgvector 0.8+) — zero manual management\n- Rebuild trigger: when orphan ratio > 20% of total entries\n\n## Domain 8: Background Worker\n- Hybrid: lazy evaluation at retrieval time + periodic batch worker (default 60min)\n- In-process tokio::spawn, not separate binary\n- Compaction rate-limited (max 10 per worker run)\n- Circuit breaker: abort if >50% operations fail\n\n## Domain 9: Working Memory Curation (RETRIEVAL LAYER — separate from tiers)\n- Tier feeds into retrieval ranking but is not the same system\n- Session/agent affinity boosts are retrieval-time concerns\n- Hot/Warm/Cold modulates retrieval score: Hot=1.0, Warm=0.5, Cold=0.1",
